@startuml DailyDangerousClassification_DatabaseFlow
title Daily Dangerous Classification - Database Flow

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam handwritten false
skinparam databaseBackgroundColor #E8F5E9
skinparam databaseBorderColor #4CAF50
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
skinparam noteBorderColor #FBC02D
skinparam activityBackgroundColor #E3F2FD
skinparam activityBorderColor #1976D2

|Service Layer|
start
:JobRun(batchSize, isLicensee);
note right
  **isLicensee Parameter**:
  - true: Process Deposit (Licensee) customers
  - false: Process Credit customers
  
  Separate runs for each type
end note

:Prepare PushDataToExternalEntity;

== Do-While Loop ==
note right
  **Pagination Loop**:
  Continue until LastCustID = 0
  Separate tracking for Deposit vs Credit
end note

repeat
  |DataAccess Layer|
  :GetDangerousClassification(isLicensee);
  
  |CTS_DataCenter (MySQL)|
  :Execute SP: **CTS_DC_DangerousDetection_GetLatest**;
  note right
    **Database**: CTS_DataCenter.ctsService
    **Timeout**: 300 seconds (default)
    
    **Purpose**: Get dangerous customers from AI/ML detection
    **Input**: @ip_IsLicensee (bool)
    
    **Query Logic**:
    ```sql
    -- Get pagination state
    SELECT Value INTO @LastCustID
    FROM CTS_SystemParameter
    WHERE ParameterKey = CASE @ip_IsLicensee
      WHEN 1 THEN 'DangerousScoreClassification_Deposit_LastCustID'
      ELSE 'DangerousScoreClassification_Credit_LastCustID'
    END
    
    SELECT Value INTO @LastScannedDate
    FROM CTS_SystemParameter
    WHERE ParameterKey = CASE @ip_IsLicensee
      WHEN 1 THEN 'DangerousScoreClassification_Deposit_LastScannedDate'
      ELSE 'DangerousScoreClassification_Credit_LastScannedDate'
    END
    
    -- First Result Set: Pagination Info
    SELECT 
      MAX(CustID) AS LastCustID,
      MAX(ClassifiedDate) AS LastScannedDate
    FROM DangerousDetection
    WHERE IsLicensee = @ip_IsLicensee
      AND CustID > @LastCustID
      AND ClassifiedDate > @LastScannedDate
      AND ClassifiedScore > @DangerousThreshold
    LIMIT 10000
    
    -- Second Result Set: Dangerous Customers
    SELECT 
      CustID,
      CTSCustID,
      SubscriberID,
      RoleID,
      CategoryID,          -- PA category
      CategoryGroup,       -- PA group
      ClassifiedDate,      -- AI detection date
      ClassifiedScore      -- Dangerous score
    FROM DangerousDetection
    WHERE IsLicensee = @ip_IsLicensee
      AND CustID > @LastCustID
      AND ClassifiedDate > @LastScannedDate
      AND ClassifiedScore > @DangerousThreshold
    ORDER BY CustID
    LIMIT 10000
    ```
    
    **Data Source**: AI/ML Detection System ⭐
    - Dangerous scores calculated by ML models
    - Stored in DangerousDetection table
    - Threshold-based filtering
    
    **Returns**: Multiple Result Sets
    1. DangerousToCCLastScannedEntity (pagination)
    2. DangerousToCCEntity[] (customers)
  end note

  |AI/ML Detection System|
  note right
    **AI/ML Process** (Upstream):
    
    1. **Data Collection**:
       - Customer betting patterns
       - Transaction history
       - Behavioral data
       - Account activity
    
    2. **ML Model Prediction**:
       - Feature extraction
       - Risk scoring algorithm
       - Dangerous score calculation
       - Confidence level
    
    3. **Storage**:
       - INSERT INTO DangerousDetection
       - ClassifiedScore (dangerous score)
       - ClassifiedDate (detection timestamp)
       - CategoryID (PA category suggestion)
    
    **Dangerous Score Factors**:
    - Betting pattern anomalies (30%)
    - Win/loss patterns (25%)
    - Transaction patterns (25%)
    - Behavioral patterns (20%)
    
    **Score Range**: 0-100 (higher = more dangerous)
    **Threshold**: e.g., > 70 = dangerous
  end note

  :Return Multiple Result Sets;
  
  |Service Layer|
  :Store DangerousToCCModel;
  note right
    **Model Contents**:
    - DangerousCCLastScanned:
      * LastCustID (pagination)
      * LastScannedDate (pagination)
    - DangerousCCs[]:
      * Customer list to process
  end note

  :Check isContinue = (LastCustID > 0);

  if (isContinue?) then (yes)
    :Transform to InsertProblemAccountEntity;
    note right
      **Transformation**:
      DangerousToCCEntity → InsertProblemAccountEntity
      
      Map:
      - CustID, CTSCustID
      - CategoryID, CategoryGroupID
      - IsLicensee (from parameter)
      - CreatedBy = StarixITId
      - **IsFromAI = true** ⭐
      - Other flags = false
    end note

    :Chunk by externalBatchSize;

    repeat
      |Service Layer|
      :InsertProblemAccountPackage(chunk);
      
      |Various DBs (via ProblemAccountServices)|
      :Insert PA Classification;
      note right
        **Insert Operations**:
        
        1. **CTSCustomerClassification** (MySQL):
           ```sql
           INSERT INTO CTSCustomerClassification
           (CustID, CategoryID, CategoryGroupID,
            IsFromAI, CreatedBy, InsertedDate, ...)
           VALUES (...)
           ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE
             CategoryID = VALUES(CategoryID),
             IsFromAI = true,
             UpdatedDate = NOW()
           ```
        
        2. **Apply PA Rules**:
           - FunctionId: DailyDangerousClassification
           - CCInputFlow: Potential
           - PA logic insertion
           - Risk scoring
        
        3. **Return**: Inserted CustIDs
        
        **Key Fields**:
        - IsFromAI = true (AI detection marker)
        - CreatedBy = StarixITId
        - CategoryID from AI prediction
      end note

      :Return Inserted CustIDs;
      
      |Service Layer|
      :PushExternalPackageByCustId(custIDs);
      
      |External - MainDB|
      :Push to MainDB API;
      note right
        **External Push**:
        
        **Purpose**: Sync dangerous classification to MainDB
        **Input**: CustIDs from PA insert
        
        **Parameters**:
        - RoleGroup: Member
        - ExternalBatchSize: chunk size
        - IsUpdateDangerToMainDB: true
        
        **Process**:
        1. Get classification data by CustIDs
        2. Format for external system
        3. POST to MainDB API endpoint
        4. Update external visibility
        5. Enable external monitoring
        
        **Batching**:
        - Chunk by ExternalBatchSize
        - Parallel push for efficiency
        - Error handling per batch
        
        **Makes Visible**:
        - Dangerous classification
        - AI detection flag
        - Risk scores
        - PA categorization
      end note

      :Return success status;

    repeat while (More chunks?) is (yes)
    -> no;

    |System Parameters|
    :Update LastCustID;
    |CTS_DataCenter (MySQL)|
    :UPDATE CTS_SystemParameter;
    note right
      **Update Query**:
      ```sql
      UPDATE CTS_SystemParameter
      SET Value = @LastCustID,
          UpdatedDate = NOW()
      WHERE ParameterKey = CASE @IsLicensee
        WHEN 1 THEN 'DangerousScoreClassification_Deposit_LastCustID'
        ELSE 'DangerousScoreClassification_Credit_LastCustID'
      END
      ```
      
      **Purpose**: Track progress for next batch
      **Enables**: Resumable processing
    end note

    |System Parameters|
    :Update LastScannedDate;
    |CTS_DataCenter (MySQL)|
    :UPDATE CTS_SystemParameter;
    note right
      **Update Query**:
      ```sql
      UPDATE CTS_SystemParameter
      SET Value = @LastScannedDate,
          UpdatedDate = NOW()
      WHERE ParameterKey = CASE @IsLicensee
        WHEN 1 THEN 'DangerousScoreClassification_Deposit_LastScannedDate'
        ELSE 'DangerousScoreClassification_Credit_LastScannedDate'
      END
      ```
      
      **Purpose**: Secondary pagination filter
      **Benefit**: Avoids re-processing by date
    end note
  else (no)
    note right
      No more dangerous customers
      for current customer type
    end note
  endif

repeat while (isContinue = true?) is (yes)
-> no;

|Service Layer|
:Complete;
note right
  **Job Completion**:
  - All dangerous customers processed
  - System parameters updated
  - Ready for next customer type run
  
  **Two Separate Runs**:
  1. Run with isLicensee = true (Deposit)
  2. Run with isLicensee = false (Credit)
end note

stop

note bottom
  **Database Architecture**:
  
  **CTS_DataCenter (MySQL)**:
  - DangerousDetection (AI/ML output storage)
  - CTSCustomerClassification (PA classification)
  - CTS_SystemParameter (pagination tracking)
  
  **AI/ML Detection System**:
  - Calculates dangerous scores
  - Predicts PA categories
  - Stores in DangerousDetection table
  - Continuous monitoring and scoring
  
  **External - MainDB**:
  - Receives dangerous classifications
  - External visibility and monitoring
  - Integration with other systems
  
  **Pagination Mechanism**:
  1. Dual keys: LastCustID + LastScannedDate
  2. Separate for Licensee and Credit
  3. System parameters store progress
  4. Resumable across job runs
  5. No risk of re-processing
  
  **Data Flow**:
  AI/ML → DangerousDetection → GetLatest → 
  Transform → InsertPA → PushMainDB → UpdateParams
  
  **Performance Considerations**:
  - Batch size: 10,000 customers per SP call
  - Chunk size: configurable for external push
  - Indexed on: IsLicensee, CustID, ClassifiedDate, ClassifiedScore
  - Efficient pagination with composite keys
  
  **Key Flags**:
  - IsFromAI = true: Marks AI detection
  - IsLicensee: Separates customer types
  - IsUpdateDangerToMainDB = true: Push enabled
end note

@enduml

